== Roasted Potato Wedges & Lemony Asparagus ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @Asparagus{6%ounce}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}. Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.)

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the asparagus then).

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, toss asparagus with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove sheet from oven; add asparagus to empty side. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add asparagus to a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack until potatoes are golden brown and asparagus is lightly browned, ~{12-15%minutes} more.

Carefully toss asparagus with lemon zest.

== Salmon ==

While veggies roast, pat @Salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat @Butter{1%tbsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon, skin sides down, and cook until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

== Creamy Dijon Chive Sauce ==

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1%unit}, half the @Dijon Mustard{2%tsp} (all for 4 servings), juice from half the lemon, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4). Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in @Sour Cream{4%tbsp}, half the chives, and @Butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until combined. (TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add more water 1 tsp at a time until it reaches a drizzling consistency.) Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide salmon, potato wedges, and asparagus between plates. Drizzle sauce over salmon. Garnish with remaining chives if desired. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.